1272
01:13:48.500 --> 01:13:50.880
many cells, and some mutations that are very rare.

1273
01:13:55.160 --> 01:13:57.660
And now that we have a probability per site,

1274
01:13:58.580 --> 01:14:00.260
in a particular tissue,

1275
01:14:01.380 --> 01:14:05.220
to want to know how many cells have this driver mutation, we just

1276
01:14:05.260 --> 01:14:06.700
have to multiply by a number of cells,

1277
01:14:07.580 --> 01:14:11.320
right? And we have many cells in our body, 36

